  "root_text": {
    "sn45.34:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 45.34 ",
    "sn45.34:0.2": "4. Paṭipattivagga ",
    "sn45.34:0.3": "Pāraṅgamasutta ",
    "sn45.34:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn45.34:1.2": "“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṁ gamanāya saṁvattanti. ",
    "sn45.34:1.3": "Katame aṭṭha? ",
    "sn45.34:1.4": "Seyyathidaṁ—sammādiṭṭhi …pe… sammāsamādhi. ",
    "sn45.34:1.5": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha dhammā bhāvitā bahulīkatā apārā pāraṁ gamanāya saṁvattantī”ti. ",
    "sn45.34:2.1": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
    "sn45.34:2.2": "Idaṁ vatvāna sugato athāparaṁ etadavoca satthā: ",
    "sn45.34:3.1": "“Appakā te manussesu, ",
    "sn45.34:3.2": "ye janā pāragāmino; ",
    "sn45.34:3.3": "Athāyaṁ itarā pajā, ",
    "sn45.34:3.4": "tīramevānudhāvati. ",
    "sn45.34:4.1": "Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte, ",
    "sn45.34:4.2": "dhamme dhammānuvattino; ",
    "sn45.34:4.3": "Te janā pāramessanti, ",
    "sn45.34:4.4": "maccudheyyaṁ suduttaraṁ. ",
    "sn45.34:5.1": "Kaṇhaṁ dhammaṁ vippahāya, ",
    "sn45.34:5.2": "sukkaṁ bhāvetha paṇḍito; ",
    "sn45.34:5.3": "Okā anokamāgamma, ",
    "sn45.34:5.4": "viveke yattha dūramaṁ. ",
    "sn45.34:6.1": "Tatrābhiratimiccheyya, ",
    "sn45.34:6.2": "hitvā kāme akiñcano; ",
    "sn45.34:6.3": "Pariyodapeyya attānaṁ, ",
    "sn45.34:6.4": "cittaklesehi paṇḍito. ",
    "sn45.34:7.1": "Yesaṁ sambodhiyaṅgesu, ",
    "sn45.34:7.2": "sammā cittaṁ subhāvitaṁ; ",
    "sn45.34:7.3": "Ādānapaṭinissagge, ",
    "sn45.34:7.4": "anupādāya ye ratā; ",
    "sn45.34:7.5": "Khīṇāsavā jutimanto, ",
    "sn45.34:7.6": "te loke parinibbutā”ti. ",
    "sn45.34:7.7": "Catutthaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn45.34:0.1": "Linked Discourses 45.34 ",
    "sn45.34:0.2": "4. Practice ",
    "sn45.34:0.3": "Going to the Far Shore ",
    "sn45.34:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn45.34:1.2": "“Mendicants, when these eight things are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore. ",
    "sn45.34:1.3": "What eight? ",
    "sn45.34:1.4": "They are right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. ",
    "sn45.34:1.5": "When these eight things are developed and cultivated they lead to going from the near shore to the far shore.” ",
    "sn45.34:2.1": "That is what the Buddha said. ",
    "sn45.34:2.2": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: ",
    "sn45.34:3.1": "“Few are those among humans ",
    "sn45.34:3.2": "who cross to the far shore. ",
    "sn45.34:3.3": "The rest just run ",
    "sn45.34:3.4": "around on the near shore. ",
    "sn45.34:4.1": "When the teaching is well explained, ",
    "sn45.34:4.2": "those who practice accordingly ",
    "sn45.34:4.3": "are the ones who will cross over ",
    "sn45.34:4.4": "Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ",
    "sn45.34:5.1": "Rid of dark qualities, ",
    "sn45.34:5.2": "an astute person should develop the bright. ",
    "sn45.34:5.3": "Leaving home behind ",
    "sn45.34:5.4": "for the seclusion so hard to enjoy, ",
    "sn45.34:6.1": "try to find satisfaction there, ",
    "sn45.34:6.2": "having left behind sensual pleasures. ",
    "sn45.34:6.3": "Owning nothing, an astute person ",
    "sn45.34:6.4": "should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions. ",
    "sn45.34:7.1": "And those whose minds are rightly developed ",
    "sn45.34:7.2": "in the awakening factors; ",
    "sn45.34:7.3": "letting go of attachments, ",
    "sn45.34:7.4": "they delight in not grasping. ",
    "sn45.34:7.5": "With defilements ended, brilliant, ",
    "sn45.34:7.6": "they are quenched in this world.” "
  },
